info.name: SocialData API
info.description:
SocialData API is a scalable and reliable API that simplifies the process of fetching data from social media websites. Currently only X (formerly Twitter) is supported.

This Postman collection serves as a "playground" to test the API endpoints and provides a number of examples for each endpoint to help you get started with the API.

This collection is not intended to replace the full documentation for SocialData API and we recommend that you refer to [http://socialdata.gitbook.io/docs](http://socialdata.gitbook.io/docs) for an up-to-date version of our documentation.

## **Getting started guide**

To start using the SocialData API Postman collection, you need to obtain your API key and update the `token` variable in Postman environment variables. All unauthenticated requests are rejected.

Follow these steps to get your API key:

1. **Sign Up**: Create an account or sign-in to the [SocialData platform](https://socialdata.tools).
    
2. **API Key**: After signing up, generate your API key in user dashboard. Keep this key confidential, as it is your private access to the API.
    
3. To edit environment variables in **Postman**, selectÂ **Environments**Â in the sidebar and select Globals. Update the initial value for `token` variable with your API key (e.g. `350|aBc...`)
    

If an API key is missing, malformed, or invalid, you will receive an HTTP 401 Unauthorized response code.

## Rate and usage limits

By default each user has a limit of 120 requests per minute shared across all endpoints. If you exceed either limit, your request will return an HTTP 429 Too Many Requests status code.

Each API response returns the following set of headers to help you identify your use status:

| Header | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `X-RateLimit-Limit` | The maximum number of requests that the consumer is permitted to make per minute. |
| `X-RateLimit-Remaining` | The number of requests remaining in the current rate limit window. |
| `X-RateLimit-Reset` | The time at which the current rate limit window resets in UTC epoch seconds. Only returned together with HTTP 429 response. |

### 500 response

An HTTP `500` response from our servers indicates that SocialData failed to retrieve the required data from Twitter and you should try again. If the outage persists, contact support at [support@socialdata.tools](https://mailto:support@socialdata.tools)

### **Need some help?**

In case you have questions, feel free to reach out to our support team at [support@socialdata.tools](https://mailto:support@socialdata.tools)

item.name: Check if User ID is following User ID

query.description: Optional. Maximum number of followers for target_user_id to look through when performing the check (used to control cost per request)

variable.description: Required. Target user id (the one being followed)

request.description:
This endpoint provides a convenient way to check if a user is following another user. This will recursively retrieve all recent followers of `target_user_id` (up to `max_count` total results) and check if the `source_user_id` is present among the retrieved followers.

ðŸ“˜ **Documentation**:

[https://socialdata.gitbook.io/docs/twitter-users/check-if-a-user-is-following-another-user](https://socialdata.gitbook.io/docs/twitter-users/check-if-a-user-is-following-another-user)

response.name: 200 Success - Follower not found

query.description: Optional. Maximum number of followers for target_user_id to look through when performing the check (used to control cost per request)

}

request.description:
Returns a tweet with an article attached to it. Output contains the same properies as tweet details endpoint, article content is returned within "article" attribute of the response.

ðŸ“˜ **Documentation:**

[https://socialdata.gitbook.io/docs/twitter-tweets/retrieve-article-details](https://socialdata.gitbook.io/docs/twitter-tweets/retrieve-article-details)

request.description:
Returns array of articles posted by the user. You can request additional results by sending another request to the same endpoint using cursor parameter.
